  "Au Gratin Potatoes|Lail Vineyards Daniel Cuvée": "Au Gratin Potatoes: this rich, creamy side's dairy-driven indulgence meets this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight. The bold red's dark-fruit weight locks into the side's fat and umami; tannin cleans the dairy. A capable pair; richness aligns if not perfectly.",
  "Au Gratin Potatoes|Laurent Perrier Le Cuvée Brut": "Champagne — clean acid, bubbles, elegant body. Too light for a manchego-cream-baked gratin; the wine disappears underneath the dish's 90-minute-bake weight. Laurent belongs with the tartare, the seafood tower, the scallops — not here.",
  "Au Gratin Potatoes|Le Ragnaie Brunello": "Au Gratin Potatoes: this rich, creamy side's dairy-driven indulgence meets this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight. The bold red's dark-fruit weight locks into the side's fat and umami; tannin cleans the dairy. A capable pair; richness aligns if not perfectly.",
