  "Blanco Tequila|Prime Tartare": "Blanco Tequila: this blanco tequila's bright, clean agave with citrus and pepper meets this rich, umami-forward starter's bold fat and concentrated savory depth. The spirit functions as a palate-setter here rather than a true counterpart to the plate. A headliner match — context-driven peak.",
  "Blanco Tequila|Roast Half Chicken": "Blanco Tequila: this blanco tequila's bright, clean agave with citrus and pepper meets this roasted chicken's savory, rich poultry-skin flavor. Spirit or liqueur alongside roasted chicken — depends on the spirit's depth. Works as a sideline pour.",
  "Blanco Tequila|Scavino Barolo": "Blanco Tequila: this blanco tequila's bright, clean agave with citrus and pepper, considered as a bridge into this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight. Avoid — the two drinks don't flow cleanly together.",
  "Blanco Tequila|Seafood Tower": "Blanco Tequila: this blanco tequila's bright, clean agave with citrus and pepper meets this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness. Neutral spirit profile means this reads as an opener, not a built pairing. Strong — clean aperitif lift.",
  "Blanco Tequila|Seared Scallops": "Blanco Tequila: this blanco tequila's bright, clean agave with citrus and pepper meets this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness. Neutral spirit profile means this reads as an opener, not a built pairing. A headliner match — context-driven peak.",
  "Blanco Tequila|Shrimp Bisque": "Blanco Tequila: this blanco tequila's bright, clean agave with citrus and pepper meets this rich, creamy seafood soup's sweet-briny depth over dairy-rich base. Clean spirit against a rich soup — the drink reads thin against the weight. Strong — the interaction lands despite the axis challenge.",
  "Blanco Tequila|Shrimp Cocktail": "Blanco Tequila: this blanco tequila's bright, clean agave with citrus and pepper meets this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness. Clean spirit against a delicate starter — aperitif-register more than pairing. A headliner match — context-driven peak.",
  "Blanco Tequila|The Tomahawk": "Blanco Tequila: this blanco tequila's bright, clean agave with citrus and pepper meets this marbled ribeye's fatty richness, smoky crust, and bold beef expression. Clean, neutral spirit on a bold steak — wrong weight class entirely. Avoid — not a steak spirit.",
  "Blended Scotch|Au Gratin Potatoes": "Blended Scotch: this blended Scotch's approachable light-smoke and versatile grain-driven profile meets this rich, creamy side's dairy-driven indulgence. Whiskey's vanilla and oak align with the side's dairy and umami depth. Works cleanly.",
  "Blended Scotch|Bone Marrow": "Blended Scotch: this blended Scotch's approachable light-smoke and versatile grain-driven profile meets this rich, umami-forward starter's bold fat and concentrated savory depth. Smoother whiskey alongside a starter — depth without dominance. Works cleanly.",
  "Blended Scotch|Brussels and Belly": "Blended Scotch: this blended Scotch's approachable light-smoke and versatile grain-driven profile meets the Brussels and Belly's smoky, sweet pork richness over bitter-char sprouts. Whiskey's vanilla and oak align with the side's dairy and umami depth. Strong — aligned weight.",
