  "Bone Marrow|Hendrick's Family": "Bone Marrow: this rich, umami-forward starter's bold fat and concentrated savory depth meets this contemporary gin's floral, fruit-forward botanical profile. Neutral spirit profile means this reads as an opener, not a built pairing. Avoid — too neutral for the plate.",
  "Bone Marrow|Highland Scotch": "Bone Marrow: this rich, umami-forward starter's bold fat and concentrated savory depth meets this Highland Scotch's honey, heather, and light-fruit character on a medium body. Smoother whiskey alongside a starter — depth without dominance. Strong — balanced opener.",
  "Bone Marrow|House Wedge": "Iceberg with house blue cheese dressing and lardons — shares the pork-belly lardon prep with our Brussels & Belly. The blue cheese dressing acid cleans the palate after the rich marrow bites; works as a cooling salad course.",
