  "Bone Marrow|Lingua Franca Avni Pinot Noir": "Willamette Pinot — low tannin, elegant dark cherry. Doesn't have the weight to match roasted marrow's richness; the wine gets lost. Steer Pinot-committed guests toward a Fisher or Sonoma Pinot that has more body.",
