  "Bone Marrow|Scavino Barolo": "Piedmont Nebbiolo — tar, dried rose, firm tannin. The high acid carves through the marrow fat and the dried rose aromatics complement the citrus salt's lift. Educate: Scavino is one of Piedmont's top names.",
  "Bone Marrow|Schloss Vollrads Riesling": "Bone Marrow: this rich, umami-forward starter's bold fat and concentrated savory depth meets this off-dry Riesling's stone-fruit sweetness and mineral backbone. Crisp or off-dry white's acidity lifts the starter — classic opening-course move. Avoid.",
