  "Bowdie's Old Fashioned|House Wedge": "Buffalo Trace, rum-soaked cherries, orange, bitters. Cocktail weight is heavier than the iceberg-and-blue-cheese wedge strictly needs, but the vanilla depth plays with bacon and the cherry brightens the dressing. Works as an opener when guest leads with whiskey.",
  "Bowdie's Old Fashioned|Il Colle Prosecco Superiore": "Bowdie's Old Fashioned: this bold whiskey-forward cocktail's oak, spice, and spirit depth, considered as a bridge into this versatile sparkling's bright acidity, toasty lees character, and cleansing bubbles. Avoid — the two drinks don't flow cleanly together.",
