  "Brussels and Belly|G.D. Vajra Moscato d'Asti": "Piedmont sweet sparkling — peach, honey, floral. The sweetness fights the brussels' bitterness and the cumin-paprika lardon rub; wrong wine on every axis. Route Moscato to dessert where it belongs.",
  "Brussels and Belly|Ghost Block Cabernet Sauvignon": "Oakville Cabernet — firm structure, classic Napa profile with dust-and-dark-fruit character. That character meets the lardons' smoky-sweet cumin-paprika rub; mid-tier Napa Cab that works beautifully with our pork-and-brussels shareable without going to the top shelf.",
  "Brussels and Belly|Ghost Block Zinfandel": "Brussels and Belly: the Brussels and Belly's smoky, sweet pork richness over bitter-char sprouts meets this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight. The bold red's dark-fruit weight locks into the side's fat and umami; tannin cleans the dairy. A headliner pair — pour confidently.",
