  "Brussels and Belly|Light / Wheated Bourbon": "Brussels and Belly: the Brussels and Belly's smoky, sweet pork richness over bitter-char sprouts meets this wheated bourbon's approachable caramel, vanilla, and soft sweetness. Whiskey's vanilla and oak align with the side's dairy and umami depth. A headliner match — context-driven peak.",
  "Brussels and Belly|Lingua Franca Avni Pinot Noir": "Willamette Pinot — dark cherry, forest floor, low tannin. Light red for a shareable that's heavier than it sounds; the Pinot's savory depth meets pork belly without overwhelming the brussels.",
  "Brussels and Belly|Lunaria Coste di Moro": "Brussels and Belly: the Brussels and Belly's smoky, sweet pork richness over bitter-char sprouts meets this medium-bodied red's approachable fruit and food-friendly acidity. The elegant red's acidity cuts the dairy fat while its cherry lifts the earthy umami. Strong — the wine refreshes the side's richness.",
