  "Brussels and Belly|Scavino Barolo": "Piedmont Nebbiolo — tar, dried rose, firm tannin. The Barolo's structure cuts through lardon fat and the high acid handles the pork belly's richness. Educate: Barolo and pork belly is a Piedmont tradition.",
  "Brussels and Belly|Scotto Cellars The Lost Chapters": "Brussels and Belly: the Brussels and Belly's smoky, sweet pork richness over bitter-char sprouts meets this medium-bodied red's approachable fruit and food-friendly acidity. The elegant red's acidity cuts the dairy fat while its cherry lifts the earthy umami. Strong — the wine refreshes the side's richness.",
