  "Brussels and Belly|Standard High-Proof Bourbon": "Brussels and Belly: the Brussels and Belly's smoky, sweet pork richness over bitter-char sprouts meets this bold, high-proof bourbon's oak spice, caramel weight, and heat. Whiskey's oak and sweetness mirror the side's dairy and umami depth. A headliner match — context-driven peak.",
  "Brussels and Belly|Stoneleigh Sauvignon Blanc": "Marlborough Sauvignon Blanc — grassy, green, light-bodied. The weight class is wrong for pork-belly lardons and cumin-paprika-cayenne rub; Stoneleigh disappears underneath the smoky depth. Keep this wine for the wedge salad or lighter starters where it fits.",
  "Brussels and Belly|Teeter Totter Cabernet Sauvignon": "Brussels and Belly: the Brussels and Belly's smoky, sweet pork richness over bitter-char sprouts meets this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight. The bold red's dark-fruit weight locks into the side's fat and umami; tannin cleans the dairy. A strong, texturally cohesive match.",
  "Brussels and Belly|Tenuta di Arceno Chianti Classico": "Brussels and Belly: the Brussels and Belly's smoky, sweet pork richness over bitter-char sprouts meets this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight. The bold red's dark-fruit weight locks into the side's fat and umami; tannin cleans the dairy. A strong, texturally cohesive match.",
  "Brussels and Belly|The BG": "Traveller bourbon, honey lavender syrup, whole-squeezed grapefruit, black walnut bitters, ginger beer. The grapefruit brightness cuts through lardon fat; black walnut bitters echo the lardon spice rub. Most refreshing whiskey cocktail on the menu.",
  "Brussels and Belly|The Manhattan": "Brussels and Belly: the Brussels and Belly's smoky, sweet pork richness over bitter-char sprouts meets this bold whiskey-forward cocktail's oak, spice, and spirit depth. Whiskey's oak and sweetness mirror the side's dairy and umami depth. Works cleanly.",
