  "Brussels and Belly|Venge Silencieux": "Brussels and Belly: the Brussels and Belly's smoky, sweet pork richness over bitter-char sprouts meets this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight. The bold red's dark-fruit weight locks into the side's fat and umami; tannin cleans the dairy. A strong, texturally cohesive match.",
  "Brussels and Belly|Vieux Carré": "Sazerac rye, Pierre Ferrand cognac, Contratto, Dom Bénédictine, Angostura, Peychaud's. NOLA classic — the rye-cognac split meets pork belly with historical weight, and the Bénédictine's herbs complement the lardon spice rub.",
  "Burrata|1881 Napa Valley": "Burrata: the burrata's creamy, fresh dairy mildness meets this medium-bodied red's approachable fruit and food-friendly acidity. The elegant red's silky frame sits alongside the starter without weight-fighting — the fruit threads through the plate. Avoid.",
  "Burrata|Aged Super-Premium Bourbon": "Burrata: the burrata's creamy, fresh dairy mildness meets this bold, high-proof bourbon's oak spice, caramel weight, and heat. The whiskey sits heavy against a starter; the match depends on whether the plate has fat to scrub. Avoid — too heavy for delicate starters.",
  "Burrata|Alexander Valley Chardonnay": "Burrata: the burrata's creamy, fresh dairy mildness meets this crisp white's citrus-driven acidity and mineral edge. Crisp or off-dry white's acidity lifts the starter — classic opening-course move. Strong — clean lift.",
