  "Burrata|Caymus Cabernet Sauvignon": "Caymus brings cocoa, mocha, and velvety tannins — entirely wrong for a light cheese-and-fruit vegetarian dish. The wine buries the burrata's delicacy and the seasonal fruit disappears under the weight. Save the bottle for the steak course.",
