  "Burrata|Domaine de Berthiers Pouilly-Fumé": "Pouilly-Fumé's flinty Loire Sauvignon Blanc. Works with the burrata but the flint character is overqualified for a lighter starter — the smoke doesn't have much in the dish to hook into. Keep for the escargot instead.",
