  "Chocolate Cake|Espresso Martini": "Tito's, espresso, Grind Espresso Liqueur, Averna amaro, vanilla syrup, Angostura. Peak coffee-chocolate pairing — espresso and coffee liqueur meet the cocoa directly, Averna's bitter backbone cuts sweetness. Currently unavailable — dessert menu pour when the cake returns.",
  "Chocolate Cake|Espresso Old Fashioned": "Buffalo Trace, Buffalo Bourbon Cream, Frangelico, espresso, brown sugar, Angostura. Coffee-forward bourbon cocktail with Frangelico hazelnut — meets the chocolate cake's cocoa density directly; brown sugar ties to the build. Peak spirit-forward pour when cake returns.",
  "Chocolate Cake|Fireball Whisky": "Chocolate Cake: this dense chocolate dessert's deep cocoa richness meets this sweet cream liqueur's dessert-adjacent lushness. Sweet liqueur's dessert-adjacent sweetness amplifies the dessert — doubles up on sugar. Works as an indulgence.",
