  "Clos Petit Ona Grenache|Brussels and Belly": "Roussillon Southern France Grenache — Clos Petit Ona, wild raspberry, kirsch, garrigue, warm spice, medium body. The warm spice plays with pork-belly fat and the garrigue matches brussels-char bitterness. Strong Southern-French for brussels-and-belly — Mediterranean polish on fat-and-char.",
  "Clos Petit Ona Grenache|Burrata": "Roussillon Southern France Grenache — Clos Petit Ona, wild raspberry, kirsch, garrigue, warm spice, medium body, low tannin. The wild raspberry bridges tomato-basil brightness and the low tannin won't tear against fresh cream. Works for burrata — a Rosé handles the dairy more cleanly.",
  "Clos Petit Ona Grenache|Cowboy Ribeye": "Roussillon Southern France Grenache — Clos Petit Ona, wild raspberry, kirsch, garrigue, warm spice, medium body, low tannin. Medium body is slightly light for Cowboy's marbled 22oz bone-in, but the warm spice handles grilled char. Works for ribeye — Grand Tinel's Châteauneuf full-body handles the cut harder.",
  "Clos Petit Ona Grenache|Crab Cake": "Never pair Clos Petit Ona with crab cake — kirsch and garrigue bury delicate lump crab and the warm spice fights the remoulade. Lead with Heitz Sauvignon Blanc's citrus lift or Reverdy Sancerre's mineral edge for shellfish clarity.",
  "Clos Petit Ona Grenache|Faroe Island Salmon": "Roussillon Southern France Grenache — Clos Petit Ona, wild raspberry, kirsch, garrigue, warm spice, medium body. The medium body matches salmon's oil-richness and the wild raspberry lifts against flesh-sweetness. Peak Southern-French for salmon — preparation changes seasonally, check with kitchen for today's build.",
  "Clos Petit Ona Grenache|Filet Mignon": "Roussillon Southern France Grenache — Clos Petit Ona, wild raspberry, kirsch, garrigue, warm spice, medium body, low tannin. The low tannin matches butter-tender filet's delicate weight and the wild raspberry plays with escargot-butter. Strong Southern-French for filet — Mediterranean lightness on the cut.",
  "Clos Petit Ona Grenache|Grilled Caesar": "Roussillon Southern France Grenache — Clos Petit Ona, wild raspberry, kirsch, garrigue, warm spice, medium body. The garrigue matches anchovy-lemon dressing and the warm spice plays against parm-char. Peak Southern-French for grilled caesar — Mediterranean herb match on the salad.",
  "Clos Petit Ona Grenache|House Wedge": "Roussillon Southern France Grenache — Clos Petit Ona, wild raspberry, kirsch, garrigue, warm spice, medium body. The warm spice plays with bacon-fat and the garrigue matches blue-cheese funk. Peak Southern-French for wedge — Mediterranean lift on the heavy salad.",
  "Clos Petit Ona Grenache|Kansas City": "Roussillon Southern France Grenache — Clos Petit Ona, wild raspberry, kirsch, garrigue, warm spice, medium body. The warm spice echoes Kansas City's lean-bold strip char and the garrigue lifts grilled beef. Strong Southern-French for the strip — Mediterranean mid-weight match.",
  "Clos Petit Ona Grenache|Laurent Perrier Le Cuvée Brut": "Never pour Clos Petit Ona in a Champagne flight — a warm-spice Grenache inside a Brut flight breaks the flight's logic and the kirsch muddies Champagne's clean bubble line. Pour each at its own course. For a garrigue-red flight, sequence through Grenache-Rhône-Bandol instead.",
  "Clos Petit Ona Grenache|Mushrooms": "Roussillon Southern France Grenache — Clos Petit Ona, wild raspberry, kirsch, garrigue, warm spice, medium body. The garrigue savory-finish echoes roasted-mushroom glutamate and the warm spice plays with butter. Peak Southern-French for mushrooms — Mediterranean herb-meets-earth match.",
  "Clos Petit Ona Grenache|Roast Half Chicken": "Roussillon Southern France Grenache — Clos Petit Ona, wild raspberry, kirsch, garrigue, warm spice, medium body, low tannin. The garrigue echoes chicken-jus herbaceousness and the warm spice plays with crispy-skin char. Peak Southern-French for the bird — preparation changes seasonally, check with kitchen for today's build.",
  "Clos Petit Ona Grenache|Sauteed Garlic Spinach": "Roussillon Southern France Grenache — Clos Petit Ona, wild raspberry, kirsch, garrigue, warm spice, medium body. The garrigue echoes garlic-oil aromatics and the medium body matches spinach-iron. Strong Southern-French for garlic spinach — Mediterranean herb-on-herb harmony.",
  "Clos Petit Ona Grenache|Seared Scallops": "Never pair Clos Petit Ona with seared scallops — garrigue and warm spice overwhelm delicate sweet shellfish and the kirsch fights browned-butter. Lead with Clos de la Chapelle Chardonnay or Rombauer's creamy richness for sear-seared harmony.",
  "Clos Petit Ona Grenache|Shrimp Bisque": "Roussillon Southern France Grenache — Clos Petit Ona, wild raspberry, kirsch, garrigue, warm spice, medium body. The medium body handles tomato-cream and the wild raspberry lifts shellfish-sweetness. Strong Southern-French for bisque — Mediterranean red-on-shellfish bridge.",
  "Clos Petit Ona Grenache|Shrimp Cocktail": "Never pair Clos Petit Ona with shrimp cocktail — cold shrimp plus cocktail-sauce horseradish gets crushed by kirsch and garrigue, and the warm spice has nowhere to land. Lead with Laurent Perrier Brut Champagne's bubble-driven palate reset.",
  "Coffee Liqueur|Beignets": "Coffee Liqueur: this sweet cream liqueur's dessert-adjacent lushness meets the beignets' light, airy, powdered-sugar sweetness. Sweet liqueur's dessert-adjacent sweetness amplifies the dessert — doubles up on sugar. Strong when the dessert is restrained.",
