  "Coffee Liqueur|Taylor Fladgate Tawny": "Coffee Liqueur: this sweet cream liqueur's dessert-adjacent lushness, considered as a bridge into this tawny port's oxidative caramel, nut, and dried-fruit complexity. A strong progression between the two drinks.",
  "Coffee Liqueur|The Tomahawk": "Coffee Liqueur: this sweet cream liqueur's dessert-adjacent lushness meets this marbled ribeye's fatty richness, smoky crust, and bold beef expression. Sweet or herbal liqueur against a savory plate — register mismatch. Avoid — not a mid-plate pour.",
  "Cognac / Brandy|Au Gratin Potatoes": "Cognac / Brandy: this cognac's grape-distilled elegance with vanilla, dried fruit, and oak meets this rich, creamy side's dairy-driven indulgence. Aged rum or cognac's sweetness and oak mirror the side's dairy-umami weight. Works cleanly.",
