  "Cowboy Ribeye|Lail Vineyards Blueprint": "Cowboy Ribeye: this marbled ribeye's fatty richness, smoky crust, and bold beef expression meets this elegant red's cherry-bright, silky-tannin frame. The elegant red's medium-light frame gets overrun by the bold, marbled steak — the wine shrinks. A weight mismatch; not the clean pairing.",
  "Cowboy Ribeye|Lail Vineyards Daniel Cuvée": "Cowboy Ribeye: this marbled ribeye's fatty richness, smoky crust, and bold beef expression meets this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight. The tannin scrubs rendered fat while dark fruit echoes the savory char. A headliner steakhouse pour.",
  "Cowboy Ribeye|Laurent Perrier Brut Rosé": "Cowboy Ribeye: this marbled ribeye's fatty richness, smoky crust, and bold beef expression meets this sparkling rosé's strawberry-and-brioche charm with crisp acidity. Bubbles scrub fat well, but sparkling lacks the dark-fruit weight and tannin for steak. Avoid — not a steak wine.",
  "Cowboy Ribeye|Le Garenne Rosé": "Pale salmon with fresh strawberry, watermelon, and a light floral note. Dry and clean with a crisp finish — a seasonal rosé meant for lighter food. The cowboy ribeye's 26oz of rich marble overwhelms it entirely. A fine opener or lunch wine, not a steak pairing.",
  "Cowboy Ribeye|Le Ragnaie Brunello": "Cowboy Ribeye: this marbled ribeye's fatty richness, smoky crust, and bold beef expression meets this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight. The tannin scrubs rendered fat while dark fruit echoes the savory char. A confident choice — steakhouse symmetry.",
