  "Crab Cake|French 75": "Inverroche gin shaken with lemon and vanilla syrup, topped with Prosecco. The bubbles and citrus reset the palate after every rich bite; vanilla softens the jalapeño heat. Celebratory pour when the guest wants a cocktail with the cake.",
  "Crab Cake|Frias Block 5": "Crab Cake: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight. Delicate seafood or mild creams buckle under the bold red's tannin. Avoid — register mismatch.",
