  "Graham's 20 Year Tawny|Cowboy Ribeye": "Never pair Graham's 20 Year Tawny with Cowboy Ribeye — twenty years of cask oxidation plus grilled-beef char collapses the wine's complexity and the residual sugar muddles marbled-ribeye savory. Lead with Silver Oak Cabernet or Caymus for the 22oz bone-in. Save the Tawny for after.",
  "Graham's 20 Year Tawny|Cream Liqueur": "Graham's 20 Year Tawny: this tawny port's oxidative caramel, nut, and dried-fruit complexity, considered as a bridge into this sweet cream liqueur's dessert-adjacent lushness. A capable cross-beverage handoff.",
  "Graham's 20 Year Tawny|Creme Brulee": "20-year oak-cask oxidative Tawny — Graham's step-up, concentrated dried fruit, roasted hazelnut, orange peel, silky long finish. The roasted hazelnut echoes torched-sugar crust caramelization and the orange peel lifts vanilla-custard. Peak step-up Tawny for creme brulee — twenty years of cask evolution on the classic match.",
