  "Honey Roasted Carrots|Alexander Valley Chardonnay": "Sonoma Chardonnay — ripe apple, pear, warm vanilla oak, smooth balanced texture. The apple-pear plays against carrots' honey-glaze sweetness and the oak-vanilla weight handles the roasted char. Strong accessible Chardonnay for honey-roasted carrots — California oak on the sweet-root classic.",
  "Honey Roasted Carrots|Caymus Cabernet Sauvignon": "Napa Rutherford Cab against a caramelized-honey roasted vegetable — concentrated cocoa-mocha body is the wrong axis for a sweet-root side. Never pair. Route Caymus to the steak course and take honey carrots with Pinot Noir, rosé, or Chardonnay.",
  "Honey Roasted Carrots|Cristom Mt Jefferson Cuvée": "Willamette Pinot — graceful Oregon Pinot with cherry, spice, medium body, structured. The structured body handles carrots' honey-glazed weight and the spice plays against the roasted char. Peak Oregon Pinot for honey-roasted carrots — Cristom structure on the sweet-root classic.",
  "Honey Roasted Carrots|Elk Cove Pinot Blanc": "Honey Roasted Carrots: these honey-roasted carrots' caramelized sweetness and earthy warmth meets this crisp white's citrus-driven acidity and mineral edge. Bright acidity lifts green vegetables; mineral lines up with the clean vegetable bite. Strong — refreshing and clean.",
  "Honey Roasted Carrots|Evening Land Seven Springs": "Willamette Pinot — savory Eola-Amity Pinot, medium tannin, elegant delicate. The savory edge plays against carrots' honey-glaze sweetness and the medium tannin meets the roasted char. Strong Oregon Pinot for honey-roasted carrots — Evening Land elegance on the sweet-root classic.",
  "Honey Roasted Carrots|Fisher Unity Pinot Noir": "Sonoma Pinot — cranberry, red cherry, baking spice, silky. The cranberry acid cuts carrots' honey-glaze sweetness and the baking spice plays against the roasted char. Works as by-the-glass Pinot for honey-roasted carrots — California silk on the sweet-root classic.",
  "Honey Roasted Carrots|Jordan Cabernet Sauvignon": "Sonoma Cab — cassis, plum, cedar, mint, fine tannin, elegant balance. The fine tannin cuts carrots' honey-glaze sweetness and the cedar plays against the roasted char. Works as approachable Cab for honey-roasted carrots — red on the sweet-root side; Pinots and Chardonnays peak higher.",
  "Honey Roasted Carrots|Keenan Chardonnay": "Spring Mountain Napa Chardonnay — green apple, lemon curd, subtle oak, bright acid. The bright acid cuts carrots' honey-glaze sweetness and the subtle oak plays against roasted-root char. Strong balanced Chardonnay for honey-roasted carrots — Napa structure on the sweet-root classic.",
  "Honey Roasted Carrots|Le Garenne Rosé": "Loire Pinot Noir rosé — delicate fresh-fruit, strawberry, crisp. The fresh fruit plays against carrots' caramelized honey sweetness and the crisp body lifts the roasted char. Peak Loire rosé for honey-roasted carrots — summer pairing on the sweet-root classic.",
  "Honey Roasted Carrots|Lingua Franca Avni Pinot Noir": "Willamette Pinot — dark cherry, forest floor, refined structure, low tannin. The low-tannin silk lifts the carrots' caramelized honey sweetness and the forest-floor earth plays against roasted-root depth. Peak Oregon Pinot for honey-roasted carrots — refined red on the sweet-root classic.",
  "Honey Roasted Carrots|Opus One": "Oakville Bordeaux blend against caramelized-honey roasted carrots — firm-tannin prestige Cab is the wrong axis for a sweet-root side. Never pair. Route Opus to the Tomahawk or Porterhouse; take honey carrots with Pinot Noir, rosé, or Chardonnay.",
  "Honey Roasted Carrots|Raventós Cava de NIT Rosé Brut": "Honey Roasted Carrots: these honey-roasted carrots' caramelized sweetness and earthy warmth meets this sparkling rosé's strawberry-and-brioche charm with crisp acidity. Sparkling acidity mirrors the vegetable's herbal brightness. Works cleanly.",
  "Honey Roasted Carrots|Scavino Barolo": "Honey Roasted Carrots: these honey-roasted carrots' caramelized sweetness and earthy warmth meets this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight. Bitter greens or sweet roots don't carry the tannin — the wine overruns the vegetable. Avoid — green and grassy flattens the bold red's fruit.",
  "Honey Roasted Carrots|Schloss Vollrads Riesling": "Honey Roasted Carrots: these honey-roasted carrots' caramelized sweetness and earthy warmth meets this off-dry Riesling's stone-fruit sweetness and mineral backbone. Bright acidity lifts green vegetables; mineral lines up with the clean vegetable bite. Works — coherent.",
