  "Jax Calesa Vineyard Pinot Noir|Bone Marrow": "Russian River Pinot against pure collagen-fat marrow — smooth Pinot lacks the tannin needed to cut the render. Never pair. Route marrow to Cabs, Bordeaux, Meritage, or structured bold reds; keep Jax Calesa for the chicken, salmon, or seafood course.",
  "Jax Calesa Vineyard Pinot Noir|Bowdie's Old Fashioned": "Russian River Pinot alongside a bourbon-forward Old Fashioned — smooth California Pinot has no hook into spirit-weight whiskey. Never layer. Keep Jax Calesa for the salmon and chicken course; route the Old Fashioned to fatted steaks, marrow, or end-of-dinner spirit service.",
  "Jax Calesa Vineyard Pinot Noir|Burrata": "Russian River Pinot — red cherry, pomegranate, subtle earth, smooth, low tannin. The soft tannin meets burrata's creamy-delicate center and the pomegranate plays against basil-tomato. Works as food-friendly Pinot for burrata — reliable red; whites and rosés peak higher.",
