  "Jax Calesa Vineyard Pinot Noir|Crab Cake": "Russian River Pinot — red cherry, pomegranate, subtle earth, low tannin, smooth. The soft tannin doesn't fight crab's sweet meat and the pomegranate plays against remoulade. Peak food-friendly Pinot for crab cake — reliable red that works where heavier reds would bury shellfish.",
