  "Jean-Pierre Grossot Chablis|Asparagus": "Burgundy Chablis — lean flint-chalk precision, green apple, citrus. The flinty mineral handles asparagus's sulfur notes and the high acid cuts the vegetal char. Peak Chablis for asparagus — Burgundian precision on the wine-tricky vegetable.",
  "Jean-Pierre Grossot Chablis|Bone Marrow": "Grossot Chablis against marrow's rendered-fat richness — lean flint-chalk precision is overwhelmed by bone depth. Never pair. Route marrow to big Cab, Manhattan, or Bowdie's Old Fashioned; keep Chablis for scallops, escargot, crab cake, or the seafood tower course.",
  "Jean-Pierre Grossot Chablis|Bowdie's Old Fashioned": "Grossot Chablis against a spirit-forward bourbon cocktail — unoaked French Chard has no hook into bold-proof whiskey. Never layer. Keep Chablis for scallops, crab cake, escargot, or the seafood course; route the Old Fashioned to fatted steaks, marrow, or end-of-dinner spirit service.",
