  "Jean-Pierre Grossot Chablis|Grilled Caesar": "Burgundy Chablis — unoaked Chard with flinty chalky minerality, lemon, green apple. The lean acidity cuts anchovy-parmesan dressing and the flint-chalk plays against grilled-romaine char. Strong classical Chablis for the Caesar — unoaked precision on the layered classic salad.",
  "Jean-Pierre Grossot Chablis|House Wedge": "Grossot Chablis — Burgundy unoaked Chardonnay, flint, chalk, lemon, green apple. The lean precise acid cuts iceberg-and-bacon and the mineral plays against blue cheese dressing. Strong Chablis for the wedge — French precision reframes the classic steakhouse salad.",
