  "Joseph Mellot Sancerre|Prime Tartare": "Joseph Mellot Sancerre — Loire Sauv Blanc benchmark, grapefruit, chalk, fresh herbs, tension finish. The refined mineral backbone meets raw prime beef's iron richness and the herbs-and-chalk frame the seasoned tartare. Peak Sancerre for tartare — precision-on-precision French pairing.",
  "Joseph Mellot Sancerre|Rainbow Trout": "Loire Sancerre — refined tension-filled mineral, citrus, flint. The flinty citrus lifts trout's delicate flaky flesh and the mineral plays against the clean freshwater character. Peak Sancerre for rainbow trout — Loire precision on the delicate classic.",
  "Joseph Mellot Sancerre|Roast Half Chicken": "Loire Sancerre — crisp refined Sauv Blanc with grapefruit, chalk, herbs, tension. The refined body handles roasted chicken; preparation changes seasonally — check with kitchen for today's build. Works well as benchmark Sancerre for chicken across most seasonal accompaniments — French classical pairing.",
  "Joseph Mellot Sancerre|Salt-Cured Halibut": "Loire Sancerre — refined tension-filled mineral, citrus, flint. The flinty citrus tension lifts halibut's firm flesh and the mineral plays against the salt-cure. Strong Sancerre for salt-cured halibut — Loire precision on the cured classic.",
  "Joseph Mellot Sancerre|Sauteed Garlic Spinach": "Joseph Mellot Sancerre — Loire Sauv Blanc with grapefruit, chalk, fresh herbs. The mineral and herb profile plays against the sauté butter-garlic and echoes spinach's earth cleanly. Works as Sancerre for the sauté side — Loire precision on a simple but well-made sauce.",
  "Joseph Mellot Sancerre|Scavino Barolo": "Loire Sancerre against Piedmont Nebbiolo's tar-and-tannin intensity — Barolo obliterates refined Sauv Blanc structure. Never layer. Route Barolo to the Tomahawk or Porterhouse and keep Sancerre for scallops, crab cake, escargot, tartare, or the classical French seafood course.",
  "Joseph Mellot Sancerre|Seafood Tower": "Loire Sancerre — benchmark Sauv Blanc with grapefruit, chalk, herbs, tension finish. The tension-filled mineral meshes with brine across oysters, shrimp, crab, and lobster and resets palate between tower elements. Strong benchmark Sauv Blanc for the tower — Loire precision for the whole shellfish platter.",
  "Joseph Mellot Sancerre|Seared Scallops": "Loire Sancerre — benchmark Sauv Blanc, crisp and refined with white grapefruit, chalk, fresh herbs, tension-filled finish. The tension-filled mineral backbone frames scallops' clean-seared sweetness and the herbs play against the pan-sear. Peak Sancerre for scallops — textbook French-on-French pairing.",
