  "Jubilation by Colgin|Burrata": "Cult Napa Cab blend against burrata's creamy-delicate center — Jubilation's firm-tannin Pritchard-Hill structure overwhelms the starter. Never pair. Route burrata to Chardonnay, Sauvignon Blanc, Rosé, or Prosecco; keep Jubilation for the steak course.",
  "Jubilation by Colgin|Cowboy Ribeye": "Jubilation — Colgin cult Napa, blackcurrant, dark chocolate, violets, espresso, firm tannin. The firm tannin handles ribeye's big marbled build and the dark-chocolate plays against the beefy char. Strong cult Napa for ribeye — Colgin prestige on the bold cut.",
  "Jubilation by Colgin|Crab Cake": "Cult Napa Cab blend against crab cake's delicate sweet meat — Jubilation's firm-tannin Colgin structure buries the shellfish. Never pair. Route crab cake to Chardonnay, Sauvignon Blanc, Rosé, or Champagne; keep Jubilation for filet, strip, or the steak course.",
  "Jubilation by Colgin|Creamed Spinach": "Jubilation — Colgin cult Napa, blackcurrant, dark chocolate, violets, espresso, firm tannin. The firm tannin cuts béchamel's dairy weight and the espresso plays against the spinach base. Strong cult Napa for creamed spinach — Colgin prestige reframes the rich steakhouse side.",
  "Jubilation by Colgin|Filet Mignon": "Jubilation — Colgin cult Napa, blackcurrant, dark chocolate, violets, espresso, firm tannin, age-worthy. The structure meets butter-tender filet's delicate sweetness and the violets-espresso play against escargot-butter. Peak cult Napa for filet — Colgin prestige on the delicate cut with proper reverence.",
