  "Lail Vineyards Daniel Cuvée|Cowboy Ribeye": "Lail flagship multi-appellation Napa Cab — dark fruit, cassis, graphite, dried violet, firm tannin, full body. The firm tannin handles ribeye's big marbled build and the cassis-graphite plays against beefy char. Peak historically-significant Napa Cab for ribeye — Daniel Cuvée named for Robin Lail's father, Mondavi-Inglenook architect.",
