  "Lingua Franca Avni Pinot Noir|Asparagus": "Willamette Pinot — dark cherry, forest floor, refined structure, low tannin. The low-tannin silk lifts asparagus's tender spears and the forest-floor earth plays against the vegetal char — the rare red that handles asparagus without clashing. Works tier on this wine's card — solid fit for Asparagus but below the wine's peaks with duck, lamb, and mushroom-sauced proteins.",
  "Lingua Franca Avni Pinot Noir|Au Gratin Potatoes": "Lingua Franca Avni Pinot Noir: this elegant red's cherry-bright, silky-tannin frame meets this rich, creamy side's dairy-driven indulgence. The elegant red's acidity cuts the dairy fat while its cherry lifts the earthy umami. Works — clean if not dominant.",
  "Lingua Franca Avni Pinot Noir|Bone Marrow": "Willamette Pinot — dark cherry, forest floor, refined structure, low tannin. Bone marrow is pure collagen fat needing tannin to cut — Pinot's low tannin can't clear the palate. Works only when guest specifically wants Pinot with marrow; Cabs and bold reds peak higher for this rich starter.",
  "Lingua Franca Avni Pinot Noir|Bone-In Filet": "Lingua Franca Avni Pinot Noir: this elegant red's cherry-bright, silky-tannin frame meets the filet's lean, buttery tenderness and delicate mineral edge. The elegant red's cherry and silky frame mirror the filet's own tenderness — mineral meets mineral, not weight-on-weight. A strong elegant match.",
  "Lingua Franca Avni Pinot Noir|Bowdie's Old Fashioned": "Willamette Pinot alongside a bourbon-forward Old Fashioned — elegant low-tannin Pinot has no hook into spirit-weight whiskey. Never layer. Keep Lingua Franca for the salmon and chicken course; route the Old Fashioned to fatted steaks, marrow, or end-of-dinner spirit service.",
  "Lingua Franca Avni Pinot Noir|Broccoli Cheddar": "Willamette Pinot — dark cherry, forest floor, refined structure, low tannin. The low-tannin silk lifts the soup's cheddar weight and the forest-floor earth plays against broccoli vegetal base. Works tier on this wine's card — solid fit for Broccoli Cheddar but below the wine's peaks with duck, lamb, and mushroom-sauced proteins.",
  "Lingua Franca Avni Pinot Noir|Broccolini": "Willamette Pinot — dark cherry, forest floor, refined structure, low tannin. The low-tannin silk lifts broccolini's tender-stem structure and the forest-floor earth plays against the vegetal char. Peaks from the dish's side; on this wine's card it's strong — below peaks with duck, lamb, and mushroom-sauced proteins. Confident pour when a guest anchors on Broccolini.",
  "Lingua Franca Avni Pinot Noir|Brussels and Belly": "Willamette Pinot — dark cherry, forest floor, spice, medium body. The acid cuts pork-belly fat and the forest-floor plays against charred brussels. Strong by-the-glass Oregon Pinot for Brussels and Belly — elegant counterpoint to the rich starter.",
  "Lingua Franca Avni Pinot Noir|Burrata": "Lingua Franca Avni Pinot Noir: this elegant red's cherry-bright, silky-tannin frame meets the burrata's creamy, fresh dairy mildness. Elegant red's cherry and silk mirror the starter's register — light-on-light or bright-on-rich depending on the plate. Works cleanly.",
  "Lingua Franca Avni Pinot Noir|Butternut Squash": "Willamette Pinot — dark cherry, forest floor, refined structure, low tannin. The low-tannin silk lifts the soup's cream weight and the forest-floor earth plays against caramelized-squash sweetness. Peaks from the dish's side; on this wine's card it's strong — below peaks with duck, lamb, and mushroom-sauced proteins. Confident pour when a guest anchors on Butternut Squash.",
  "Lingua Franca Avni Pinot Noir|Chilean Seabass": "Willamette Pinot — dark cherry, forest floor, refined structure, low tannin. The low-tannin silk lifts seabass's buttery flesh and the forest-floor earth plays against the rich texture. Peak Oregon Pinot for Chilean seabass — refined red on the buttery classic.",
  "Lingua Franca Avni Pinot Noir|Clam Chowder": "Willamette Pinot — dark cherry, forest floor, refined structure, low tannin. The low-tannin silk lifts the chowder's cream weight and the forest-floor earth plays against bacon-potato base. Works tier on this wine's card — solid fit for Clam Chowder but below the wine's peaks with duck, lamb, and mushroom-sauced proteins.",
  "Lingua Franca Avni Pinot Noir|Cowboy Ribeye": "Willamette Pinot — dark cherry, forest floor, spice, medium body, low tannin. The refined structure underserves the big marbled ribeye — Pinot's low tannin falls short of the cut's fat-and-char demand. Works when guest wants lighter red with ribeye; Cabs peak higher.",
  "Lingua Franca Avni Pinot Noir|Crab Cake": "Willamette Pinot — dark cherry, forest floor, spice, refined structure, low tannin. The soft tannin doesn't fight crab's sweet meat and the forest-floor earth plays against remoulade. Peak by-the-glass Pinot for crab cake — unconventional red that works where heavier reds would bury the shellfish.",
  "Lingua Franca Avni Pinot Noir|Creamed Spinach": "Willamette Pinot — dark cherry, forest floor, whisper of spice. The acid cuts béchamel's dairy weight and the forest-floor earth plays against the spinach base. Strong by-the-glass Pinot for creamed spinach — Oregon elegance reframes the rich steakhouse side.",
  "Lingua Franca Avni Pinot Noir|Creamy Potato": "Willamette Pinot — dark cherry, forest floor, refined structure, low tannin. The low-tannin silk lifts the soup's cream-potato weight and the forest-floor earth plays against the dairy base. Works tier on this wine's card — solid fit for Creamy Potato but below the wine's peaks with duck, lamb, and mushroom-sauced proteins.",
