  "Mushrooms|Bruichladdich": "Mushrooms: this earthy, umami-packed side's mushroom-and-truffle depth meets this Islay Scotch's intense peat smoke, medicinal phenol, and bold weight. Whiskey's oak and sweetness mirror the side's dairy and umami depth. A headliner match — context-driven peak.",
  "Mushrooms|Cade Cabernet Sauvignon": "Mushrooms: this earthy, umami-packed side's mushroom-and-truffle depth meets this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight. The bold red's dark-fruit weight locks into the side's fat and umami; tannin cleans the dairy. A strong, texturally cohesive match.",
  "Mushrooms|Canadian Whisky": "Mushrooms: this earthy, umami-packed side's mushroom-and-truffle depth meets this Canadian whisky's smooth, light grain profile. Whiskey's vanilla and oak align with the side's dairy and umami depth. A headliner match — context-driven peak.",
  "Mushrooms|Caymus Cabernet Sauvignon": "Caymus — cocoa, mocha, velvety tannins. The full Napa Cab meets mushroom's umami depth; the tannin holds against the earthy weight. Peak Cab pour when mushrooms are the side alongside a steak.",
  "Mushrooms|Château Batailley": "Mushrooms: this earthy, umami-packed side's mushroom-and-truffle depth meets this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight. The bold red's dark-fruit weight locks into the side's fat and umami; tannin cleans the dairy. A headliner pair — pour confidently.",
  "Mushrooms|Château Beaucastel": "Mushrooms: this earthy, umami-packed side's mushroom-and-truffle depth meets this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight. The bold red's dark-fruit weight locks into the side's fat and umami; tannin cleans the dairy. A headliner pair — pour confidently.",
  "Mushrooms|Château Gombaude-Guillot": "Pomerol Merlot-Cab Franc — Château Gombaude-Guillot, biodynamic Pomerol, 2016, dark plum, truffle, mocha, velvety finish. The truffle note echoes mushroom umami directly and velvety Merlot wraps garlic-butter glaze. Works for mushroom side — plush Pomerol on the earthy side where Scavino Barolo peaks harder.",
  "Mushrooms|Château Haut Segottes": "Mushrooms: this earthy, umami-packed side's mushroom-and-truffle depth meets this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight. The bold red's dark-fruit weight locks into the side's fat and umami; tannin cleans the dairy. A headliner pair — pour confidently.",
