  "Odette Cabernet Sauvignon|The Tomahawk": "Odette — Stags Leap Cab, dark fruit, sage, cedar, graphite, refined tannin. The velvet-glove body meets Tomahawk fat and char and the sage-cedar frames the theatrical bone-in cut. Strong refined Cab for Tomahawk — iron-fist-velvet-glove balance, though Opus or Shafer Hillside peak higher for the biggest steak.",
  "Odette Cabernet Sauvignon|Truffle Fries": "Odette — Stags Leap Cab, dark fruit, sage, cedar, graphite, refined. The velvet-glove body frames truffle-fry earth and the sage-cedar cuts the crisp oil-and-salt. Peak refined Stags Leap Cab for truffle fries — iron-fist-velvet-glove balance meets the decadent side with herbal complexity.",
  "Opus One|Asparagus": "Opus One: this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight meets this light, green vegetable's clean herbal edge. Bitter greens or sweet roots don't carry the tannin — the wine overruns the vegetable. Avoid — green and grassy flattens the bold red's fruit.",
  "Opus One|Au Gratin Potatoes": "Opus One — Oakville Bordeaux blend, dark fruit, mocha, cedar, dried violet, firm tannin. The firm tannin cuts gruyère-cream weight and the mocha plays against the lactic richness. Works as collector Napa blend for au gratin — prestige wine on the cheesy side.",
  "Opus One|Bee's Knees": "Opus One: this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight, considered as a bridge into this gin cocktail's citrus brightness and botanical lift. Avoid — the two drinks don't flow cleanly together.",
  "Opus One|Beignets": "Opus One: this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight meets the beignets' light, airy, powdered-sugar sweetness. Creamy vanilla or airy beignets get run over by bold-red tannin. Avoid — the dessert is too delicate.",
  "Opus One|Blanco Tequila": "Opus One: this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight, considered as a bridge into this blanco tequila's bright, clean agave with citrus and pepper. Avoid — the two drinks don't flow cleanly together.",
  "Opus One|Bone Marrow": "Opus One — Oakville Bordeaux blend, dark fruit, mocha, cedar, dried violet, firm tannin. The firm tannin cuts marrow's collagen fat and the mocha-cedar plays against the smoky mineral depth. Peak collector Napa blend for marrow — Mondavi-Rothschild prestige on the rich starter.",
  "Opus One|Bone-In Filet": "Opus One — Oakville Bordeaux blend, dark fruit, mocha, cedar, dried violet, firm tannin. The firm tannin handles bone-in filet's intensified beefy edge and the cedar plays against the bone-deepened cut. Peak collector Napa blend for bone-in filet — Mondavi-Rothschild prestige for the elevated cut.",
