  "Opus One|Escargot": "Opus One: this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight meets this rich, umami-forward starter's bold fat and concentrated savory depth. Richness from the plate and structure from the wine share the same register — a savory weight-on-weight setup. Not the sharpest pairing.",
  "Opus One|Faroe Island Salmon": "Opus One: this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight meets this rich, fatty seafood's buttery flesh and delicate-yet-substantial texture. The bold red's tannin shreds the fish's delicate flake, and the dark fruit clashes with briny sweetness. Textbook avoid — this is the classic red-meat-only territory.",
  "Opus One|Filet Mignon": "Opus One — Oakville Bordeaux blend, dark fruit, mocha, cedar, dried violet, firm tannin, impeccably balanced. The balanced structure meets butter-tender filet's delicate sweetness and the mocha plays against escargot-butter. Peak collector Napa blend for filet — sell the Mondavi-Rothschild story on the delicate cut.",
