  "Opus One|Salt-Cured Halibut": "Opus One: this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight meets this delicate seafood's mild, flaky flesh. The bold red's tannin shreds the fish's delicate flake, and the dark fruit clashes with briny sweetness. Textbook avoid — this is the classic red-meat-only territory.",
  "Opus One|Sauteed Garlic Spinach": "Opus One: this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight meets this light, green vegetable's clean herbal edge. Bitter greens or sweet roots don't carry the tannin — the wine overruns the vegetable. Avoid — green and grassy flattens the bold red's fruit.",
  "Opus One|Seafood Tower": "Opus One: this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight meets this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness. Delicate seafood or mild creams buckle under the bold red's tannin. Avoid — register mismatch.",
  "Opus One|Seared Scallops": "Collector Napa Cab blend against scallop sweetness — Opus One's firm-tannin Bordeaux blend buries the delicate shellfish. Never pair. Route scallops to Chardonnay, Sauvignon Blanc, Riesling, or Rosé; keep Opus One for the steak course.",
  "Opus One|Shrimp Bisque": "Opus One: this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight meets this rich, creamy seafood soup's sweet-briny depth over dairy-rich base. Bold red meets rich, caramelized depth — the wine's dark fruit threads through the savory base. Not a clean fit — the soup's register clashes.",
  "Opus One|Shrimp Cocktail": "Opus One: this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight meets this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness. Delicate seafood or mild creams buckle under the bold red's tannin. Avoid — register mismatch.",
