  "Seafood Tower|Local Michigan Gin": "Seafood Tower: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets this contemporary gin's floral, fruit-forward botanical profile. The spirit functions as a palate-setter here rather than a true counterpart to the plate. Strong — clean aperitif lift.",
  "Seafood Tower|London Dry Gin": "Seafood Tower: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets this London Dry gin's juniper-forward, citrus-herbal frame. Clean spirit against a delicate starter — aperitif-register more than pairing. A headliner match — context-driven peak.",
  "Seafood Tower|Margarita": "Seafood Tower: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets this bright tequila cocktail's citrus lift and agave backbone. Light cocktail and delicate starter share the same register — fresh opener. Strong — aligned brightness.",
  "Seafood Tower|Nut Liqueur": "Seafood Tower: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets this sweet cream liqueur's dessert-adjacent lushness. Liqueur sweetness or herbal complexity against a starter — wrong register typically. Avoid — not a starter pair.",
  "Seafood Tower|Opus One": "Mondavi-Rothschild's $950 prestige Cabernet — completely wrong weight class for cold shellfish. The wine buries every element of the tower. Never pour here; reserve Opus for the steak course where it can perform.",
  "Seafood Tower|Pablo Sour": "Seafood Tower: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets this bright tequila cocktail's citrus lift and agave backbone. Light cocktail and delicate starter share the same register — fresh opener. Strong — aligned brightness.",
  "Seafood Tower|Paloma": "Seafood Tower: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets this bright tequila cocktail's citrus lift and agave backbone. Both lean bright and clean — no weight fighting weight, just an easy start to the meal. Strong — aligned brightness.",
  "Seafood Tower|Paul Bara Grand Rosé Brut": "Grower Champagne from Bouzy — more savory and Pinot-forward than Laurent Perrier. Peak match for the tower's mixed shellfish and the three sauces; the extra body handles the lobster component where a lighter Champagne thins out.",
  "Seafood Tower|Pierre Gimonnet Special Club Brut": "Seafood Tower: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets this versatile sparkling's bright acidity, toasty lees character, and cleansing bubbles. Sparkling's bubbles and acid scrub the starter's fat while the bright frame lifts the plate. A headliner starter pour.",
  "Seafood Tower|Pommery Cuvée Louise": "Seafood Tower: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets this prestige Champagne's layered complexity — toasty lees, fine mousse, and mineral depth. Sparkling's bubbles and acid scrub the starter's fat while the bright frame lifts the plate. A headliner starter pour.",
  "Seafood Tower|Raventós Cava de NIT Rosé Brut": "Rosé Cava — sparkling, red-fruit character, bright acid. Handles our mignonette's red-wine-vinegar sharpness and the cocktail-sauce horseradish heat without fighting the shellfish. Smart alternative when the table doesn't want Champagne.",
  "Seafood Tower|Robert Moncuit Les Grand Blancs": "Seafood Tower: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets this versatile sparkling's bright acidity, toasty lees character, and cleansing bubbles. Sparkling's bubbles and acid scrub the starter's fat while the bright frame lifts the plate. A headliner starter pour.",
  "Seafood Tower|Scavino Barolo": "Piedmont Nebbiolo with tar, dried rose, and firm tannin. Aggressive structure against delicate cold seafood; the Barolo bullies the tower's nuance. Save this bottle for the Tomahawk or the Filet.",
  "Seafood Tower|Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin": "Seafood Tower: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets this contemporary gin's floral, fruit-forward botanical profile. Clean spirit against a delicate starter — aperitif-register more than pairing. Strong — clean aperitif lift.",
  "Seafood Tower|St Supéry Sauvignon Blanc": "Napa Sauvignon Blanc — grassy, citrus-forward. Similar function to the Sancerre but California-forward. Bright acid delivers across the full tower of oysters, crab, shrimp, lobster. Pick when the guest prefers American producers over French.",
  "Seafood Tower|Stoneleigh Sauvignon Blanc": "Seafood Tower: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets this crisp white's citrus-driven acidity and mineral edge. Crisp or off-dry white's acidity lifts the starter — classic opening-course move. Strong — clean lift.",
  "Seafood Tower|Vesper": "Seafood Tower: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets this dry, spirit-forward gin cocktail's bitter-herbal complexity. Light cocktail and delicate starter share the same register — fresh opener. A headliner match — context-driven peak.",
  "Seafood Tower|Veuve Clicquot Brut": "Recognizable name, yellow-fruit character, soft toast notes. Easier pour for the guest who wants Champagne but not to study the bottle. Handles the tower cleanly — not as precise as Laurent but broadly liked.",
  "Seafood Tower|White / Light Rum": "Seafood Tower: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets this white rum's clean sugarcane, tropical lift, and light frame. Neutral spirit profile means this reads as an opener, not a built pairing. Strong — clean aperitif lift.",
