  "Seared Scallops|Opus One": "Mondavi-Rothschild's $950 prestige Cabernet. Far too much structure for scallops; the pour buries whatever the kitchen builds today. Steer Opus to the steak course — never waste it on a seared-shellfish starter.",
  "Seared Scallops|Our Lady of Guadalupe Acolytes": "Seared Scallops: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets this crisp white's citrus-driven acidity and mineral edge. Crisp or off-dry white's acidity lifts the starter — classic opening-course move. A headliner opener.",
