  "Shrimp Cocktail|St Supéry Sauvignon Blanc": "Napa Sauvignon Blanc — grassy, citrus-forward. The grass note echoes our watercress puree's vegetal character, and the bright acid cuts through the cocktail sauce's horseradish. Clean California pour when the guest wants American over Loire.",
  "Shrimp Cocktail|St Supéry Élu Meritage": "Shrimp Cocktail: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight. Delicate seafood or mild creams buckle under the bold red's tannin. Avoid — register mismatch.",
  "Shrimp Cocktail|Standard High-Proof Bourbon": "Shrimp Cocktail: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets this bold, high-proof bourbon's oak spice, caramel weight, and heat. Bold whiskey's weight meets the starter — register depends on the plate's richness. Avoid — too heavy for delicate starters.",
  "Shrimp Cocktail|Stoneleigh Sauvignon Blanc": "Marlborough Sauvignon Blanc, classic green and citrus. Bright and cold, matches the chilled shrimp's temperature and bite. Approachable entry-point for the guest who isn't looking to spend up on the white list.",
  "Shrimp Cocktail|Teeter Totter Cabernet Sauvignon": "Shrimp Cocktail: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight. Delicate seafood or mild creams buckle under the bold red's tannin. Avoid — register mismatch.",
