  "Simon Family Estate Reserve|Kansas City": "Boutique Napa family estate Cab — dark plum, cassis, toasted oak, long refined finish, firm tannin. The firm tannin meets Kansas City's lean-bold marbled strip and the cassis plays against beefy char. Peak boutique Napa Cab for the strip — Simon Family estate-grown pedigree on the American cut.",
  "Simon Family Estate Reserve|Mushrooms": "Boutique Napa family estate Cab — dark plum, cassis, toasted oak, long refined finish, firm tannin. The toasted oak echoes roasted-mushroom glutamate and the dark plum plays against the earth depth. Strong boutique Napa Cab for mushrooms — Simon Family estate structure on the earthy side.",
  "Simon Family Estate Reserve|Porterhouse": "Boutique Napa family estate Cab — dark plum, cassis, toasted oak, long refined finish, firm tannin. The firm tannin handles Porterhouse's dual strip-and-filet and the cassis plays against both lean-and-fatty sides. Strong boutique Napa Cab for Porterhouse — Simon Family pedigree on the dual-cut classic.",
  "Simon Family Estate Reserve|Seared Scallops": "Boutique Napa estate Cab against scallop sweetness — Estate Reserve's firm-tannin plum-cassis structure buries the delicate shellfish. Never pair. Route scallops to Chardonnay, Sauvignon Blanc, Riesling, or Rosé; keep Estate Reserve for the steak course.",
  "Simon Family Estate Reserve|Shrimp Cocktail": "Boutique Napa estate Cab against cold raw shrimp with horseradish — firm-tannin Estate Reserve and chilled shellfish with cocktail sauce is textbook clash. Never pair. Route shrimp cocktail to Chardonnay, Sauvignon Blanc, Rosé, or Champagne; keep Estate Reserve for the steak course.",
  "Simon Family Estate Reserve|The Tomahawk": "Boutique Napa family estate Cab — dark plum, cassis, toasted oak, long refined finish, firm tannin, full body. The firm tannin handles Tomahawk's massive bone-in ribeye and the toasted oak plays against smoky char. Peak boutique Napa Cab for Tomahawk — Simon Family estate-grown fruit and reserve-level winemaking on the grand cut.",
  "Simon Family Estate Reserve|Truffle Fries": "Boutique Napa family estate Cab — dark plum, cassis, toasted oak, long refined finish, firm tannin. The firm tannin cuts truffle-fry potato fat and the toasted oak plays against the truffle-oil umami. Peak boutique Napa Cab for truffle fries — Simon Family reserve-level structure on the umami hit.",
  "Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin|Beignets": "Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin: this contemporary gin's floral, fruit-forward botanical profile meets the beignets' light, airy, powdered-sugar sweetness. Neutral or botanical spirit against sweet dessert — the drink can go harsh and medicinal. A headliner when the dessert leans herbal or citrus-bright.",
  "Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin|Bone Marrow": "Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin: this contemporary gin's floral, fruit-forward botanical profile meets this rich, umami-forward starter's bold fat and concentrated savory depth. Clean spirit against a delicate starter — aperitif-register more than pairing. Avoid — too neutral for the plate.",
  "Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin|Bowdie's Old Fashioned": "Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin: this contemporary gin's floral, fruit-forward botanical profile, considered as a bridge into this bold whiskey-forward cocktail's oak, spice, and spirit depth. Avoid — the two drinks don't flow cleanly together.",
  "Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin|Burrata": "Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin: this contemporary gin's floral, fruit-forward botanical profile meets the burrata's creamy, fresh dairy mildness. Clean spirit against a delicate starter — aperitif-register more than pairing. A headliner match — context-driven peak.",
  "Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin|Caymus Cabernet Sauvignon": "Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin: this contemporary gin's floral, fruit-forward botanical profile, considered as a bridge into this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight. Avoid — the two drinks don't flow cleanly together.",
  "Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin|Cheesecake": "Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin: this contemporary gin's floral, fruit-forward botanical profile meets the cheesecake's dense, tangy dairy richness. Neutral or botanical spirit against sweet dessert — the drink can go harsh and medicinal. Works for the botanical-forward guest.",
  "Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin|Cowboy Ribeye": "Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin: this contemporary gin's floral, fruit-forward botanical profile meets this marbled ribeye's fatty richness, smoky crust, and bold beef expression. Clean, neutral spirit on a bold steak — wrong weight class entirely. Avoid — not a steak spirit.",
  "Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin|Crab Cake": "Smooth citrus gin with the crab cake — Aviation or Bluecoat's softer juniper lets the crab lead and the citrus brightness threads through the remoulade. Gateway gin pairing; works even for guests who typically don't order gin with food.",
  "Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin|Escargot": "Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin: this contemporary gin's floral, fruit-forward botanical profile meets this rich, umami-forward starter's bold fat and concentrated savory depth. Neutral spirit profile means this reads as an opener, not a built pairing. Works as a preceding pour.",
  "Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin|Faroe Island Salmon": "Smooth craft gin with the salmon — Gray Whale or Empress 1908's restraint and citrus lift the salmon's richness without competing. Empress is also the theatrical pour — the color change in the glass sells itself tableside.",
  "Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin|Filet Mignon": "Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin: this contemporary gin's floral, fruit-forward botanical profile meets the filet's lean, buttery tenderness and delicate mineral edge. Clean, neutral spirit on a bold steak — wrong weight class entirely. Works as a preceding pour.",
  "Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin|Grilled Caesar": "Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin: this contemporary gin's floral, fruit-forward botanical profile meets the Grilled Caesar's charred romaine, anchovy umami, and bold creamy dressing. Spirit or liqueur against the Caesar's umami and char — depends on the spirit's weight whether it lands. Works as a parallel pour.",
  "Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin|House Wedge": "Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin: this contemporary gin's floral, fruit-forward botanical profile meets the House Wedge's crisp iceberg against creamy bleu dressing. Clean spirit against a crisp salad — the drink reads aperitif, not pairing. Strong — the interaction lands despite the axis challenge.",
  "Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin|Prime Tartare": "Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin: this contemporary gin's floral, fruit-forward botanical profile meets this rich, umami-forward starter's bold fat and concentrated savory depth. Neutral spirit profile means this reads as an opener, not a built pairing. Strong — clean aperitif lift.",
  "Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin|Roast Half Chicken": "Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin: this contemporary gin's floral, fruit-forward botanical profile meets this roasted chicken's savory, rich poultry-skin flavor. Spirit or liqueur alongside roasted chicken — depends on the spirit's depth. Strong — the spirit mirrors the poultry's depth.",
  "Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin|Scavino Barolo": "Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin: this contemporary gin's floral, fruit-forward botanical profile, considered as a bridge into this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight. Avoid — the two drinks don't flow cleanly together.",
  "Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin|Seafood Tower": "Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin: this contemporary gin's floral, fruit-forward botanical profile meets this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness. The spirit functions as a palate-setter here rather than a true counterpart to the plate. Strong — clean aperitif lift.",
  "Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin|Seared Scallops": "Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin: this contemporary gin's floral, fruit-forward botanical profile meets this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness. Neutral spirit profile means this reads as an opener, not a built pairing. A headliner match — context-driven peak.",
