  "St Supéry Cabernet Sauvignon|Au Gratin Potatoes": "St Supéry — Napa Cab with blackberry, cassis, mocha, full body. The firm tannin cuts au gratin's cheese-and-cream weight and the mocha plays against the golden crust. Strong by-the-glass Cab for au gratin — Rutherford character frames the indulgent side at accessible price.",
  "St Supéry Cabernet Sauvignon|Bone Marrow": "Napa Rutherford Cab — blackberry, cassis, mocha, firm tannin. The full body meets marrow's rendered-fat richness and the mocha-tannin frames the bone depth. Works as by-the-glass Cab for marrow — classic Napa character, though premium Cabs like Silver Oak or Caymus peak higher for the starter.",
  "St Supéry Cabernet Sauvignon|Brussels and Belly": "Napa Rutherford Cab — blackberry, cassis, mocha, firm tannin. The full body handles pork-belly fat and the mocha plays against charred brussels. Strong by-the-glass Cab for Brussels and Belly — classic Napa character cuts through the rich starter at accessible price.",
  "St Supéry Cabernet Sauvignon|Burrata": "Napa Rutherford Cab against burrata's creamy-delicate center — firm-tannin full body crushes the milk and basil-tomato-pistachio clashes with cassis-mocha. Never pair. Route burrata to rosé, Pinot Blanc, or Sancerre and keep St Supéry for the steak course.",
  "St Supéry Cabernet Sauvignon|Cowboy Ribeye": "Napa Rutherford Cab — blackberry, cassis, mocha, firm tannin. The firm structure handles Cowboy's marbled bone-in richness and the mocha meets rendered fat. Strong by-the-glass Cab for Cowboy — classic Napa character, though bigger Cabs like Silver Oak or Caymus peak higher for the fattest ribeye.",
  "St Supéry Cabernet Sauvignon|Crab Cake": "Napa Rutherford Cab against crab cake's delicate sweet shellfish — firm-tannin full body crushes remoulade-and-crab and the mocha clashes with sweet meat. Never pair. Route crab cake to Chablis, Sancerre, or Champagne and keep St Supéry for the steak course where its Napa character shines.",
  "St Supéry Cabernet Sauvignon|Creamed Spinach": "St Supéry — Napa Cab with blackberry, cassis, mocha, firm tannin. The full body cuts creamed spinach's dairy weight and the mocha plays against the earthy sauce. Peak by-the-glass Cab for creamed spinach — Rutherford character frames the classic steakhouse side at accessible price.",
  "St Supéry Cabernet Sauvignon|Filet Mignon": "Napa Rutherford Cab — blackberry, cassis, mocha, firm tannin, full body. The firm structure meets butter-tender filet's lean sweetness and the cassis plays against escargot-butter toppers cleanly. Peak by-the-glass Cab for filet — classic Rutherford Cab character at an accessible price.",
  "St Supéry Cabernet Sauvignon|Grilled Caesar": "Napa Rutherford Cab — blackberry, cassis, mocha, firm tannin. The full body meets anchovy-parmesan dressing and the mocha-tannin plays against grilled-romaine char. Strong by-the-glass Cab for grilled Caesar — a red pairing that works on the layered classic salad.",
