  "Stoneleigh Sauvignon Blanc|Creamed Spinach": "Stoneleigh Sauvignon Blanc: this crisp white's citrus-driven acidity and mineral edge meets this rich, creamy side's dairy-driven indulgence. Crisp white acidity cuts dairy richness — palate-cleansing counterpoint. Avoid.",
  "Stoneleigh Sauvignon Blanc|Escargot": "Marlborough NZ Sauv Blanc — passionfruit, grapefruit, grass, zesty acidity. The zesty acid cuts escargot's garlic-parsley butter and the tropical-citrus plays against the snail richness. Strong accessible NZ Sauv Blanc for escargot — approachable by-the-glass pour on the French classic.",
  "Stoneleigh Sauvignon Blanc|Faroe Island Salmon": "Marlborough NZ Sauv Blanc — passionfruit, grapefruit, grass, zesty acidity. The zesty acid cuts salmon's oil-rich flesh; preparation changes seasonally — check with kitchen for today's build. Works as accessible NZ Sauv Blanc for salmon across most seasonal builds — by-the-glass reliability.",
  "Stoneleigh Sauvignon Blanc|Filet Mignon": "Stoneleigh Sauvignon Blanc: this crisp white's citrus-driven acidity and mineral edge meets the filet's lean, buttery tenderness and delicate mineral edge. Lean white acidity can't balance steakhouse fat — the wine disappears against the char. Avoid — not a steak wine.",
  "Stoneleigh Sauvignon Blanc|French Onion": "Stoneleigh Sauvignon Blanc: this crisp white's citrus-driven acidity and mineral edge meets the French Onion's caramelized umami, beef broth, and crusty-cheese finish. The wine's acidity cuts the cream, but its weight doesn't carry the soup. Avoid — outmatched.",
  "Stoneleigh Sauvignon Blanc|Grilled Caesar": "Stoneleigh — Marlborough NZ Sauv Blanc, passionfruit, grapefruit, grass, zesty. The zesty acid cuts anchovy-parmesan dressing and the tropical-citrus plays against grilled-romaine char. Strong accessible NZ Sauv Blanc for grilled Caesar — reliable by-the-glass pour on the layered classic.",
  "Stoneleigh Sauvignon Blanc|Gumbo": "Marlborough NZ Sauv Blanc against a dark-roux Cajun stew — zesty passionfruit-grass has no weight to meet gumbo's roux-and-andouille depth. Never pair. Route Stoneleigh to the wedge, burrata, or seafood starters; take gumbo with Rioja, CdP, Super Tuscan, or Zinfandel.",
  "Stoneleigh Sauvignon Blanc|Honey Roasted Carrots": "Stoneleigh Sauvignon Blanc: this crisp white's citrus-driven acidity and mineral edge meets these honey-roasted carrots' caramelized sweetness and earthy warmth. Bright acidity lifts green vegetables; mineral lines up with the clean vegetable bite. Avoid.",
  "Stoneleigh Sauvignon Blanc|House Wedge": "Marlborough Sauvignon Blanc — classic NZ with passionfruit, grapefruit, fresh-cut grass, zesty acidity. The zesty acid cuts iceberg-and-bacon weight and the passionfruit-grapefruit plays against blue cheese dressing. Peak by-the-glass Sauv Blanc for the wedge — reliable bright crowd-pleaser on the classic.",
